<br>
&lt;Insert personal rant here&gt;<br>
Eating a death is not fun, but guess what sometimes you have to. I ate yet another one on Saturday because I was too damned stubborn to gate away from a blue mob. That's my fault. At no point did it ever occur to me to start sending tells to people I don't know and who are not even in the same zone to help me recover from MY mistake. When I did try creating a cleric, I must have missed the screen that stated that I HAD to res anyone who wanted one. <br>
<br>
I don't care if you drag your rotting corpse over and drop it on my boots, I still have absolutely no obligation to do anything about it. Especially if my group is engaged in combat or recovering from combat.<br>
<br>
As a shaman, I will not travel across a zone just to buff someone, no matter how much you beg or what names you call me. If I were a cleric and I was busy doing ANYTHING at all that I find more interesting than resing you, I might not take ten steps to the left to res you. Call me names or get in my face and I absolutely will not do anything for you. In fact I'd rather stand there and offer free reses to anyone else in the zone than res you. Sorry everyone. Rude people make me almost as angry as stupid people. <br>
&lt;End personal rant&gt;<br>
<br>
Ladi S, I wish you had posted the names of these people so I know who NOT to help in the future. Keep in mind that most of us schlubs who can't res have no hard feelings if you happen to be near but cannot res us. AND we sure as hell appreciate the drive-by reses that some clerics drop on our dead selves occasionally. At least that's how I feel.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ustratdregar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>strat dregar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://files.mrfixitonline.com/moodstamps/237.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(7/17/01 1:56:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.gigahosts.com/~c1003/aimicons/icons/3dstuff/militaryflags/marines.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hmmm</span><hr size=1> yeah im sure every clr has had this kindda thing happen to them i have been through this many times.  some people just &quot;cant uderstand&quot; for some reason.<br>
